  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Twin/Double Rooms</strong> sleep two people and are around 14-16m². Some of these rooms have a <strong>special offer</strong> price which are on a first come first served basis.</p>
<p><strong>Triple Rooms</strong> sleep three people and are around 14-16m². This room can be made up as a double and one single bed, or as three single beds.</p>
<p><strong>Quad Rooms</strong> sleep four people, are around 28-32m² with interconnecting twin bedrooms.</p>
<p><strong>Quin Rooms</strong> sleep five people, are around 28-32m² and are made up of an interconnecting twin and a triple room.</p>
<p>Rooms must be occupied to full occupancy in French school holiday dates (Christmas, New Year, February and Easter) and rooms may be allocated according to family size outside of these dates.</p>
<p>All rooms are available with a <strong>piste view</strong>, at a supplement. To guarantee a piste view please make sure you book that specific room type.</p>
<p><strong>Bedroom facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Twin or double beds (please specify preference when booking)</li>
<li>Bath with shower head attachment or shower room</li>
<li>Separate WC</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Toiletries</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Bed linen</li>
<li>Towels</li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Daily house keeping</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
